10.body:
pub enum Unit { Ch(f64), Cm(f64), Dpi(f64), Dpcm(f64), Dppx(f64), Em(f64), Fr(f64), In(f64) Mm(f64), Pc(f64), Pt(f64), Px(f64), Q(f64), Rem(f64), Vh(f64), Vmax(f64), Vmin(f64), Vw(f64),
} Units Follows CSS Values 3 drafted in csswg.org, if we don't use Unit.X() in number field, Elvis will choose Unit.Px by default. Absolute Lengths unit name equivalence cm centermeters 1cm = 96px/2.54 mm millimeters 1mm == 1/10th of 1cm Q quarter-millimeters 1Q = 1/40th of 1cm in inches 1in = 2.54cm = 96px pc picas 1pc = 1/6th of 1in pt points 1pt = 1/72th of 1in px pixels 1px = 1/96th of 1in Relative Lengths unit relative to em font size of element ex x-height of element's font ch width of the "0" (ZERO, U+0030) glyph in the element‚Äôs font rem font size of the root element vw 1% of viewport‚Äôs width vh 1% of viewport‚Äôs height vmin 1% of viewport‚Äôs smaller dimension vmax 1% of viewport‚Äôs larger dimension Others unit represents dpi Dots per inch dpcm Dots per centmeter dppx Dots per px unit fr This unit represents one fraction of the available space in the grid container.

pub enum GridAutoRows { Auto(Unit, Option<Unit>), Fixed(Unit),

27.body:
pub enum GridTemplate { Plain(Vec<Unit>), Repeat(i32, Unit),
} In the Plain section, Vec's length will be the column count of grid, and every Unit is the width of each column, Repeat just make this easier, every child are in the same width.
